# Bond Data Profiler Skill

## Purpose
Profile bond datasets for carry strategy development.

## Trigger
Use when asked to "profile", "scan", or "analyze" bond data.

## Workflow
1. Scan directory for .csv, .parquet, .gz files
2. Identify columns per column-mappings.md
3. Generate reports/{dataset_name}_summary.md
4. Generate reports/{dataset_name}_gaps.md
5. Update reports/INDEX.md

## Carry-Specific Requirements
In addition to standard profiling, flag:
- OAS availability (required for carry calc)
- Duration availability (required for carry calc)
- Yield fields (ytm, yield_to_worst, oas_yield)
- Funding rate proxies (if present)
- Rating coverage (for IG filtering)

## Output Schema Recommendation
After profiling, suggest column mapping for:
- bond_universe.py loader
- carry signal inputs

## References
- See column-mappings.md for field heuristics
- See CLAUDE.md for project conventions
